# =============================================================================
# Member Convex project — copy this file to `.env.member.local` and fill in.
# =============================================================================
# In Convex Dashboard: open the PROJECT that owns your MEMBER URL
# (same host as VITE_CONVEX_URL_MEMBER, e.g. https://xxxx.convex.cloud).
#
# Then: Project settings → find "CLI", "Deploy", "Developer", or "Deployment"
# and copy ONE of the linking options below (whatever the dashboard shows).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option A — deployment selector (most common for `npx convex deploy`)
# Must look like:   prod:mild-hedgehog-2   or   dev:something-123
# Do NOT paste the full URL (https://….convex.cloud) — that breaks the CLI (404).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=prod:YOUR_DEPLOYMENT_SLUG

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Option B — production deploy key (some workflows use this instead)
# Paste only if the dashboard gives you a deploy key and not CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CONVEX_DEPLOY_KEY=
